review_blob: A nice, light cider -- sparkling and tart with a fruity aroma.  Clean and great in the hot weather, particularly with grilled chicken and fish.
One of my favorite ciders -- have had approx. 10 bottles over the last 3 years.  Pours like a cider, but tastes a bit like a lambic -- sour notes along the lines of a gueze.
beer_name: Farnum Hill Kingston Black Reserve Cider

review_blob: Excelleny Framoise, sour notes of fruit and rotting wood.  Like a forest floor dampened by unicorn tears...

Bottle purchased from Alesmith in July.  Opened 2 months later while brewing Ranier Cherry Stout.  Simply put, amazing.  Deep woody, chocolatey notes, complex flavors inc. coffee, choc., alcohol, leather, anise, vanilla.  Thin head, mouthfeel perhaps a little too smooth for the body.
beer_name: AleSmith Speedway Stout - Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: Not as hoppy as I expected.  12oz, opened @ home.  Almost treacley, a little maltier than first expected, but overall a superb pour... Obvious alcohol notes. Like a drinkable scotch.
